Name: ia-amygdala
Description: Modulates emotional processing of memory, conditioning, and reactions

Name: ia-caudnuc
Description: Involved in procedural learning, motor processing, and executive functioning.

Name: ia-cerebellum
Description: Plays important role in motor control and motor learning

Name: ia-eyeballs
Description: Receive light information and pass it on to the brain

Name: ia-fornix
Description: Implicated in memory and a major output tract of the hippocampus

Name: ia-hippocampus
Description: Controls remembering episodic memories, spatial navigation

Name: ia-pons
Description: Conducts signals thalamus & lower brain, performs a multitude of other functions

Name: ia-putamen
Description: Associated with motor processes, learning, and inhibition

Name: ia-thalamus
Description: A hub which relays sensory information between different parts of the cortex

Name: ia-hypothalamus
Description: Responsible for several autonomic functions, such as homeostasis, appetite, and sleep

Name: ia-infcollic
Description: Receives sound information from the auditory cortex and brainstem nuclei.

Name: ia-supcollic
Description: Processes  preliminary visual data and controls reflexive eye movements

Name: ia-pyramid
Description: Involved in the control of motor functions

Name: ia-medulla
Description: Responsible for many autonomic functions, including respiration, cardiac, & vasomotor system

Name: ia-globus
Description: Involved in the regulation of involuntary movement.
